cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.ET, cs.PL, cs.SY

This paper deals with the development of efficient algorithms and data structures for dynamic reconfiguration of a partially reconfigurable FPGA. This involves the segmentation of the chip area and the adjustment of communication infrastructure. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.AR (Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.ET (Embedded Systems), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). However, given the focus on data structures and algorithms, cs.DS is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because they involve aspects of the problem, such as hardware architecture, programming languages, and control systems.
